{"word":"ἀγγαρεύω","slug":"ἀγγαρεύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἀγγαρεύω</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <el>ἄγγαρος</el> ‘mounted courier’ in Persia] ‘compel or force to do <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ someth.\">someth.</a>’, with military nuance associated with the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Lat.\">Lat.</a> angario = press into service: <b><i>commandeer, requisition</i> <a href='B:470 27:32'>Mt 27:32</a>; <a href='B:480 15:21'>Mk 15:21</a>;</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ prob.\">prob.</a> also <b><a href='B:470 5:41'>Mt 5:41</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Ἁγάρ\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀγγεῖον\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}